- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a format to describe synthesis problems via Linear Temporal Logic (LTL), which is a logic used in computer science.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents a high-level format to describe synthesis problems, which can be seen as a programming language.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper presents a tool to automatically translate the format into plain LTL, which can be used for synthesis by a solver, and software engineering often involves the development of tools to automate tasks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents a format to describe synthesis problems, which is a common problem in AI, and the tool presented can be used to synthesize controllers for autonomous systems.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper presents a format to describe synthesis problems via LTL, which is a formal language used to specify temporal properties of systems.
